< Text>
Minuteman Press is simply a Blessing! Two weeks ago I placed an order and forgot. I had a program made and on a Friday night it hit me, I forgot to pick up my programs. 300 programs sitting at the store and it was 5:45pm. The store closed at 5pm and closed on the weekends.  I called in a panic and left a message. A employee called me back and said come by and pick them up and I could pay later. < Text>
I am writing this on behalf of my 87 year- old great aunt who purchased a car at Sam Linder Honda on 10/26/18.

My great aunt was rear ended in her 2007 Honda CR-V and wanted to purchase another Honda since they are such reliable cars.

She was shown a 2017 Honda HR-V EX w/ navigation (top of the line model) with 3,081 miles. She ended up purchasing the car in cash, wrote a check that day and drove home in her new car. I received a call that she bought a new car and wanted me to see it, I went to her house and saw the car.

She showed me the long, yellow paper which is referred to as the sales contract. I was surprised to see that in line 1a (cost before any tax, fees, etc) that she paid $26,487.74 for the vehicle. On the Honda website the MSRP of a new 2018 model was $26,540. A new one would be $52.26 more than a year old HR-V. She also got a 7 year/75,000 mile warranty for $2,235.

I looked in the glovebox to find the manual and discovered an envelope of papers. I assumed they were my great aunt's and gave them to her. She said it was a sales contract with another persons name on it. We discovered that the woman who purchased the car new one year before left her sales contract in the car. That concerned me being that the car was certified preowned and they didn't check the glovebox, did they check everything else under the hood? Upon opening it up I saw that on line 1a she paid $25,146.00 when the car was new with 59 miles on it and only $1,845 for the same warranty. My great aunt paid $1,341.74 MORE for the exact same car than the first owner did (excluding warranty).

My father, great aunt and I called and spoke to the general sales manager, Al Feria, who was very nice and helpful.

I asked why this car cost more than a new car and he explained that the two plants that produce the EX w/ navigation were out of commission which made that particular model in high demand due to there not being a lot of them. He said that the same day my aunt purchased two other people came in looking to buy it. I looked and found a like model without AWD for $21,500 with 11,000 miles on it.

I brought up that the dealership failed to check the glovebox and left the contract in it from the old owner. The phone disconnected shortly after stating the above but Al immediately returned my call. He said that some employee was getting written up for leaving the contract in the glovebox which is unfortunate but I would be furious if my personal information was left for people to find.

He kept asking how we can fix the situation and I said take the car back. He offered us $23,000 to take the car back which would have been a huge loss in money. I told him that we would would get back to him regarding the warranty and said I was going to post this online for others to see. He then began explaining all the great things Sam Linder does for the community and that he'd take the review personally. I politely ended the call by saying that nothing else needed to be said and I was getting frustrated.

Call it what you want, but I feel that my great aunt was taken advantage of and essentially got ripped off.< /Text>

<Rating>5</Rating>< review>
$2.50 for 5 minutes (nothing less). Cash only and remember to bring cash! This self car wash is wonderful. Only 1-2 people were there during my wash and I was able to take all the time I need. The pressure hose is very strong and got rid of a lot of gunk that I would normally have to scrub off. I only used the presoak, pressure water, and spotless rinse. The area is well maintained, kept clean, and in a nice quiet neighborhood.

If you want to spend $5 to clean your car, this place is the place to go to. Just remember to plan around the limited time and enjoy a clean car!<//review>

<UserId.>115938271670498215051<//UserId.>< username>
Kiera Tierney Giles<//username>
<Time>1613781329285< /Time><Rate>4<//Rate>< Text>
They have a 7 room bed and breakfast with 3 hot tubs. And several rental homes. We rented the 1 bedroom rental house called the bunkhouse. It has a fully equipped kitchen with a coffee pot, a shower, space heater that looks like a fireplace. Even bath robes for your private hot tub just outside the front door. The views are incredible from everywhere in and outside the house. We even watched Buffalo grazing from our natural springs hot tub. There's an small ghost Town with neat stuff to look at and an old cemetery up the hill.<//Text>

None</pictures>
<text>Camped at Benton Hot Springs for two nights. Due to Covid restrictions I never went into a building. Registration was outside and contactless. Specific instructions about proper campground etiquette were written down with a signed agreement and a copy for guests. Each campsite had its own tub and was as private as physically possible without constructing a complete barrier around the tubs. The campsite tubs are drained and cleaned after guests depart. The campground is clean and free of litter. Reservations are months out, and all campsites are full.  This is a little gem on a less traveled road.</text>< Date>

5<//Rating>
< text>
Love our stay at the Tub Sites!

As a hot spring afficionado, I had to visit the Benton Hot Springs. We stayed for one night, tub was super clean and the temperature was perfect to soak for hours without getting overheated. There's nothing better than sitting in the hot tub at night with the crisp air around you, watching the stars for hours.

Bring a robe and extra towels with you if you're camping.

Will definitely be back again in the future to spend a full day.<//text>

< review>
Friendly accommodating staff there to welcome you. Comfy eclectic settings and clean rooms. Many clean hot springs tubs to choose from with soft fluffy robes available for use. Located in lovely shaded desert setting. Shaded outdoor seating available under big leafy trees. There is even a very friendly feline there that loves to be petted.
Great way to meet people from different walks of life and share a wonderful deliciously  prepared breakfast in the morning. Two breakfast times to choose from, 8 or 9 AM.< /review>

<UserId.>117366387172873440049<//UserId.>< Name>
diana hsieh< /Name>
<Time>1584640353116<//Time>< Rating>
4</Rating>
< review>
Camping at Benton hot springs was a worthy challenge.  Online reservations were easy, though I wish there was more info on particular sites.  Nonetheless I booked site 3 which was very relaxing, each site seemed to have its own uniqueness and privacy.  it rained/snowed on our arrival night which made things a bit cold and wet. Travel dates middle of March 2020, Chains were not required.  Light snow, ice cold temps overnight, and partly sunny days.  It was nice to arrive with tub being filled with hot water. Odorless, very hot water. (Warning for those who are sensitive to hot soaking temps) Camp site had bbq and fire pit, picnic table.  No wood to be bought on site.  Actually nothing to be bought on site so bring everything in. Otherwise a grocery store is in bishop (40 mins away) no cell signal or WiFi unless you‚Äôre staying at the ‚Äúinn‚Äù also breakfast is not included for guests staying at campsites or cabin rentals.  Bring your ez up. The best things about Benton hot springs:  Dogs allowed, Each campsite has its own private tub, & clothing optional.
For the price to camp in freezing wet temps, I would expect at least shower facilities or toilet, not Porto potties. Also some signage or information on water properties, etc. front desk staff was not very helpful.  They did not ask once how our water temp was or anything, and it was scalding at first.  Though I am pretty self sufficient I could see how guests would have a hard time navigating to their site if arriving after dark.  But the experience and hot springs makes things well worth the stay.<//review>

This absolutely wonderful place offers quant rentals, cute vintage decorated rooms, family style meals and a charming self-guiding walking tour of the surrounding buildings and history of the town of Benton. With perfect views of the White Mountains, there is much to learn, and enjoy while visiting. The hot spring tubs are clean, and the soothing water is untreated and fresh. The inn staff is warm and accommodating. I'll absolutely be back again! What a gem!<//Text>

<Review>I stayed at the Benton hot springs last week on my cycling journey across the west from Colorado to California. The people who work here are the most caring folks in the world. when I arrived, I had a huge cut on my left leg from a collision I had had on the road during the night. I didn't have large bandages to cover the wound, but one of the ladies who works at the inn drove 38 miles to the town of Bishop where's the nearest pharmacy to get the bandages, a saline spray, neosporing, and some gummy beans for me. she went way above what was required or expected of her, and she made a huge difference for me to be able to ride the next 300 miles to San Francisco. Theresa, you are my savior and my angel! I would not have made it to the end without you. I will pay your generosity forward to someone else who is in need, and will treat them with the same care and love you showed me. <Rate>4<//Rate>< review>
Stayed here after a long day of motorcycle riding. The hostess was friendly and helpful upon our arrival. The hot springs were so relaxing after a long day on the road. The grounds are well kept with lots of nice little areas to hang out outside. They have a couple of nice patios and a barbecue for lunch and dinners. We stayed in the Marquessa Suite...the room has great charm, beds were comfortable and the room was clean. The TV had terrible sound but not a deal breaker. For those of you who care, the WiFi was very slow, but you cant complain since this is the middle of nowhere. I've stayed at other B&B's and the breakfast here was just ok. All in all I'm planning on staying here again as it was an enjoyable and relaxing time.< /review>

<Time>1579824027211<//Time><Name>Michael Boehnlein< /Name><GmapID>0x80db68cf3f185461:0xbe976456233449c3< /GmapID><Resp>None<//Resp>< text>
The Technician was very nice, and kept me completely informed throughout the process. The MRI machine they use is not the typical cylinder that feels like a coffin. Instead, it's like a top and bottom hamburger bun, and you slide into the middle. This design allowed for looking around to either side, and was much more comfortable. The machine let's you know when each scan starts so you can be aware of how many more to go until you are done.

Now, the negatives. Really, only one negative, and that's the lack of headphones/music. It's not the end of the world, but during 40 minutes in the machine would have been nicer with some relaxing tunes.< /text>
